cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the problem of nonparametric estimation of information divergence functionals, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields in computer science. However, the focus on kernel density estimation and the use of optimally weighted ensemble estimation techniques suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The use of machine learning techniques and the application to classification problems also suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The use of optimization techniques and the analysis of convergence rates suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as possible sub-categories as well.
